data.title: Closed for good at this address
data.text: We came to Subway looking to have lunch, but when we arrived, we found that Subway has been closed at this address.  There is no mention of this location on the Subway website.  There is a Japanese restaurant at this address.

data.title: food
data.text: I stopped there for a breakfast sandwich, the sandwich was good but I was disappointed that I had to pay extra for avocado or spinach, especially during avocado  season should have to pay extra.

data.title: Typical Subway, easy access and good parking
data.text: This is a typical Subway store featuring everything as advertised. No surprises. It does have a great location at Rand Road and Miner Street (Dempster) in Des Plaines, just off the I 294 tollway exit ramp. It is easy to park there and I have never seen a long line, so the service is quick.

data.title: Late night visit but server was very Fresh!!
data.text: delighted with the courtesy!! made my sub the way i wanted! the place was very clean!! now i know where to go for late dinner or bite.

data.title: Nice for outdoor dining!!
data.text: The outdoor eating area is very pleasant and surprisingly secluded even though it overlooks a busy street.  There is a very large pine tree that gives shade and protection from the afternoon sun and the many flowers surrounding the tables are something you don't expect at a Subway.  There's a nice view across the street of the forest preserve if you overlook the funeral home.  It's a lovely building if you can bring yourself to forget about the purpose of it.  We've had many meals out there and have seen deer on a few occasions and even a coyote.  A nature lover's Subway!!

data.title: Un clasico
data.text: Riquisimos los sandwiches, el lugar es muy lindo, los combos tienen precios accesibles, la gente muy amable
